'''City court''' or '''municipal court''' is a [[court of law]] with [[jurisdiction]] limited to a [[city]] or other [[municipality]]. It typically addresses "violations of [[Local ordinance|city ordinances]] and may also have jurisdiction over minor criminal cases...and over certain civil cases."<ref name="Gifis">{{cite book|author=Steven H. Gifis|title=Dictionary of Legal Terms |edition= 5th |year=2016 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=vBpjCwAAQBAJ|publisher=[[Barron's Educational Series]] |location=New York |isbn=978-1-4380-6796-4}}</ref><ref name="Ballentine1916">{{cite book|author=James A. Ballentine |title=A Law Dictionary |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=C288AAAAIAAJ&pg=PA318& |year=1916|publisher=[[Bobbs-Merrill]] |location=Indianapolis, USA }}</ref> Examples include [[Moscow City Court]] in Russia, Municipal Court of Chicago<ref name="Goldfield2006">{{cite book|editor= [[David Goldfield]] |title=Encyclopedia of American Urban History|year= 2006|publisher=SAGE Publications|isbn=978-1-4522-6553-7 |chapter=Criminal Justice System |pages=197–198 |author=David B. Wolcott |chapterurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=4il1AwAAQBAJ&pg=PT236 }}</ref><ref name=IL-JudicialTimeline>{{cite web |url=http://www.19thcircuitcourt.state.il.us/1289/Timeline-of-Judicial-History |work=History of the Illinois Courts |title=Timeline of Judicial History |accessdate=September 15, 2016 |publisher=Nineteenth [[Illinois circuit courts|Judicial Circuit Court]], Lake County, Illinois |location=Waukegan, IL }}</ref> and [[New York City Civil Court]] in the United States.
