'''Farm tin''' or the '''tin dues''' was one of a number of payments required of [[tin]] miners in [[Devon]] and [[Cornwall]].  The holder of a [[mining sett]] was required to pay a portion of the [[black tin]] extracted to the holder of the [[tin bounds]] in which the sett was granted. The portion was the "farm tin".<ref>Bainbridge (1867) p.62</ref> The portion was normally interpreted to be one-twelfth of extracted tin: they were also required to play [[toll tin]], calculated at one fifteenth.<ref>Gunning (1833) p.197</ref>

