{{Infobox company | name = Plain Green Loans, LLC | logo = | type = [[Private company|Private]] | foundation = | founder = | location_city = [[Montana]] | location_country = [[United States]] | key_people = | industry = [[Financial services]] | products = [[Payday lending]] | num_employees = | owner = [[Chippewa Cree|Chippewa Cree Tribe]] | homepage = {{URL|http://www.plaingreenloans.com}} }}
'''Plain Green Loans''' is an online [[installment loan]] company providing emergency cash via the internet. It is a [[Tribal Lending Enterprise]] owned by the [[Chippewa Cree|Chippewa Cree Tribe]] on the [[Rocky Boy Indian Reservation]].<ref name="havredaily">{{cite news | url=http://www.havredailynews.com/news/story-397399.html | title=Havre Daily News | work=PDL Ventures in last days, Rocky Boy tribal rep says | date=November 3, 2011 | accessdate=December 27, 2011 | author=Leeds, Tim | location=Havre, Montana | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111118153236/http://www.havredailynews.com/news/story-397399.html | archivedate=November 18, 2011 | df= }}</ref><ref name="missoulian">{{cite news | url=http://missoulian.com/news/state-and-regional/chippewa-cree-tribe-cashes-in-on-high-interest-online-loans/article_4360b0b6-2fe7-11e1-bfb5-001871e3ce6c.html | title=Missoulian | work=Chippewa Cree tribe cashes in on high-interest online loans | date=Dec 27, 2011 | agency=[[Associated Press]] | accessdate=December 27, 2011 | author=Volz, Matt | location=Missoula, Montana}}</ref> Plain Green Loans (PGL) is a online resource for the short-term financial needs of [[underbanked]] and subprime consumers. By offering bi-weekly and monthly installment loans, Plain Green helps consumers meet their emergency, cash-flow needs quickly and online. Plain Green markets, underwrites, and services its own portfolio.
==History== In 2011, Plain Green Loans issued over 121,000 loans.<ref name = "missoulian"/> Because the Chippewa Cree Tribe is a [[Sovereignty|sovereign nation]] which enjoys tribal immunity, it is not subject to state laws which seek to prevent [[usury]] by regulating high-interest lending.<ref name="guardian">{{cite news | url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/feedarticle/10012473 | title= The Guardian | work=Tribe's high-interest online lending venture booms | date=December 26, 2011 | agency=AP Foreign | accessdate=December 27, 2011 | author=Volz, Matt | location=London, England}}</ref>
In February 2012, a coalition of Indian tribes welcomed a Colorado court ruling that tribal immunity has no territorial boundaries.<ref>{{cite news|title=Indian tribes welcome ruling on sovereignty |url=http://www.denverpost.com/breakingnews/ci_19968984|accessdate=15 February 2012|newspaper=Denver Post|date=15 February 2012}}</ref>
In 2014, several members of the tribe were convicted of illegally siphoning seven percent of the company's revenues which totaled $25 million over a three-year period.<ref name="funneled">{{cite news|url=http://flatheadbeacon.com/2014/09/09/chippewa-cree-tribal-members-funneled-cash-lending-company/|title=Chippewa Cree Tribal Members Funneled Cash from Lending Company|date=September 9, 2014|accessdate=21 June 2015|agency=Associated Press}}</ref>
In January 2018, there was a successful settlement was reported between Plain Green Loans and BEH Gaming Ltd related to loans to the Chippewa Cree Tribe and Chippewa Cree Tribe Development Corporation. The settlement and Plain Green’s payment of the debt to BEH releases the Chippewa Cree Tribe and Chippewa Cree Tribe Development Corporation from all liability. The agreement settles a lawsuit filed by Florida-based BEH Gaming Ltd in 2014 (Case # DV-14-142 in the 12th Judicial District Court in Hill County, Montana) to repay loans to expand Northern Winz Hotel and Casino. <ref> Ross, Alex (January 5, 2018). “Havre Daily News”. Plain Green settles with BEH over loan lawsuit.</ref>{{citation needed|date=April 2018}}
==Operations== Plain Green has a B rating with the [[Better Business Bureau]]"<ref>{{cite news|title=Better Business Bureau Plain Green Rating |url=http://www.bbb.org/eastern-washington/business-reviews/payday-loans/plain-green-loans-in-box-elder-mt-1000003260/|accessdate=6 June 2015|website=Better Business Bureau|date=1 January 2015}}</ref>
